# Git Ignore for AI OS Projects

This `.gitignore` file is recommended for projects using AI OS framework.

```gitignore
# Environment Variables
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# IDE / Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.sublime-workspace
.cursor/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST
.venv/
venv/
ENV/
env/

# Node.js
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm
.eslintcache

# Database
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.postgres
pgdata/

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# Temporary AI OS Session Files
AIChat.*.md
*_session_*.md

# OS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Misc
.cache/
.tmp/

# Keep these tracked
!.env.example
!.env.sample
```

## Usage

Create this file in your project root:

```bash
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourusername/ai-os/main/.gitignore-template > .gitignore
# or copy the content above
```

## Example Workflow

```bash
# Initialize git
git init

# Create .gitignore
echo "[content above]" > .gitignore

# Stage files (excluding .gitignore patterns)
git add .

# Initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: AI OS framework setup"

# Push to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/my-project.git
git push -u origin main
```

## Important: Track These Files

Always track these for collaboration:
- ✅ `CONTEXT.md` — project definition (shared)
- ✅ `PROJECT_PLAN.md` — agent configuration (shared)
- ✅ `STATE.md` — project state (shared)
- ✅ `AGENTS.md` — framework (shared)
- ✅ `COMMANDS.md` — commands reference (shared)
- ✅ `RULES.md` — coding standards (shared)
- ✅ `WORKFLOWS.md` — execution flows (shared)

## Don't Track These

Never commit:
- ❌ `.env` — has secrets
- ❌ `node_modules/` — large, regenerable
- ❌ `__pycache__/` — compiled Python
- ❌ `.venv/` — virtual environment
- ❌ `.sqlite` databases — data files

## Commit Examples

```bash
# Feature development
git add backend/models.py backend/routes.py
git commit -m "Phase 2: Implement user authentication"

# Update state
git add STATE.md
git commit -m "Update: Completed auth implementation"

# Bug fix
git add backend/auth.py
git commit -m "Fix: Handle expired JWT tokens properly"

# Configuration
git add CONTEXT.md
git commit -m "Update: Add PostgreSQL to tech stack"

# Deployment ready
git add Dockerfile docker-compose.yml
git commit -m "Deploy: Docker configuration for Railway"
```

---

**Happy version control! 🎯**
